 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are tasked with accurately classifying short, user-submitted texts related to financial and banking activities into precisely one predefined category. Each input text will describe a distinct banking or financial situation. Your goal is to assign the correct SINGLE label from the provided list of allowed categories, based on the exact situation described.\n\n### List of Categories (Use only one per text; match spelling exactly):\nautomatic_top_up, balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer, beneficiary_not_allowed, cancel_transfer, card_payment_fee_charged, card_payment_not_recognised, declined_cash_withdrawal, exchange_rate, exchange_via_app, failed_transfer, get_disposable_virtual_card, get_physical_card, passcode_forgotten, pending_top_up, pending_transfer, receiving_money, reverted_card_payment?, top_up_by_cash_or_cheque, top_up_reverted, topping_up_by_card, transfer_fee_charged, transfer_into_account, transfer_timing, verify_my_identity, verify_source_of_funds\n\n### Your classification instructions:\n\n1. **One Label Only**: Assign exactly one label that directly matches the situation described. Do not use multiple labels or alter labels from the list.\n\n2. **Match to Most Specific Action or Issue**: Choose the most precise and specific category available, based on the financial action or problem described. Prioritize an outcome or direct process over broader or related terms.\n\n3. **Be Domain-Specific**: Understand financial terminology:\n   - \"Cancel_transfer\": Use ONLY when the user is explicitly asking about, requesting, or reporting the act of canceling a transfer or payment THEY initiated.\n   - \"Top_up_reverted\": Select ONLY when a deposit/top-up action has failed, been reversed, canceled by the system, or refunded due to system/bank error or external cause (not due to a conscious user-initiated cancellation). Includes cases reporting chargebacks or involuntary payment reversals for added funds.\n   - \"Receiving_money\": Use for ALL cases regarding receiving incoming money (salaries, bank transfers, deposits, etc.) UNLESS the text focuses on a failed, reversed, or pending state (then pick the more specific label, e.g., \"pending_transfer,\" \"failed_transfer,\" or \"top_up_reverted\").\n   - \"Exchange_via_app\": ONLY use for questions or reports specifically about exchanging (converting) currency **using the app** interface.\n   - \"Exchange_rate\": ONLY use when the text is about the rate of exchange/conversion value.\n   - \"Get_physical_card\": Use for requests or questions about obtaining a physical (plastic) card, including setup of PIN for physical cards.\n   - \"Passcode_forgotten\": Use only for scenarios where the user has forgotten their passcode/PIN and needs recovery—do **not** use for PIN setup on new or replacement cards.\n\n4. **Disambiguation**: When in doubt between related categories:\n   - Choose the label that indicates the most exact, direct financial result or process.\n   - If the text is ambiguous on whether an action failed or is still waiting, use pending labels (e.g., \"pending_transfer\").\n   - Do not select a category just because of superficial word matches; read for the actual banking context.\n\n5. **Card and PIN Handling**:\n   - For questions about setting up a PIN for a new or replacement physical card, use \"get_physical_card\" even if the wording alludes to a PIN. Only use \"passcode_forgotten\" if the user cannot remember an existing PIN/passcode.\n\n6. **Formatting**:\n   - Respond to each text input with only the category label (verbatim from the list), and no additional explanation or commentary.\n\n### Example Clarifications:\n- If a user asks if they need to exchange a currency before depositing a salary, assign \"receiving_money\".\n- If a user is reporting that a deposit/top-up was reversed or failed (unless they themselves canceled it), assign \"top_up_reverted\".\n- If a user asks how to exchange money via your app specifically, assign \"exchange_via_app\".\n- If a user asks about setting up a PIN for a new card, assign \"get_physical_card\" (not \"passcode_forgotten\").\n\n**Always re-read the input for banking context and process details, and assign only the most specific, matching label.**"
 },
